06:37.419 --> 06:41.082
Let me get ten Nine Lives,
four Lucky Ducks, two Straight Pokers...

06:41.190 --> 06:43.317
three Crabpots and five Powerballs.

06:44.092 --> 06:45.992
Thank you, here you go.

06:51.066 --> 06:53.193
You all need to stop.

06:58.740 --> 07:00.571
Why are all these people clapping?

07:00.642 --> 07:03.236
-You didn't see me on the news?
-No, l didn't.

07:03.412 --> 07:05.380
I got meat!

07:05.514 --> 07:09.143
More beef than East Coast, West Coast rap.
Check it out!

07:10.152 --> 07:12.416
Superman! Saving lives and stuff.

07:12.487 --> 07:14.717
Why don't you cop
one of these pork chops?

07:14.790 --> 07:18.021
Know what you need to do?
You need to leave. I won't tell you again.

07:18.093 --> 07:21.426
Nobody wants your meat.
Who the hell wants to buy stolen meat?

07:21.496 --> 07:23.896
-I'll take a T-bone.
-You like gizzards, too?

07:26.802 --> 07:29.532
Did you hear about that guy
running for President?

07:29.605 --> 07:31.232
Who will replace him?

07:31.306 --> 07:34.207
Maybe they should get Shaq.
Nobody can beat him.

07:34.276 --> 07:36.676
Are you getting gas?
You're holding my line up.

07:36.745 --> 07:38.110
Yeah, l'm sorry.

07:38.847 --> 07:40.041
$10 on three.

07:50.692 --> 07:53.160
You've got a lot of nerve hanging up on me.

07:53.228 --> 07:54.354
Hanging up?

07:54.496 --> 07:57.761
-What's going on?
-I'm leaving you! That's what's going on.

07:57.833 --> 08:01.667
The only reason l accepted this engagement
ring from you in the first place...

08:01.737 --> 08:04.604
is because l thought you had potential!

08:04.673 --> 08:06.937
I thought you wanted more!

08:07.242 --> 08:10.643
Why can't you just play the game?
Wear a suit!

08:10.946 --> 08:12.811
Be a real politician!

08:12.881 --> 08:16.180
What's my clothes have to do with....
Are you seeing somebody else?

08:16.251 --> 08:18.276
I'm seeing everybody else!

08:19.154 --> 08:21.987
I've met mosquitoes
with more force than you.

08:22.057 --> 08:26.016
I'm tired of your little games,
tired of being your little secretary.

08:26.094 --> 08:28.187
Here's the light bill. I didn't pay it.

08:28.263 --> 08:30.697
Here's the cable bill. I didn't pay that, either.

08:30.766 --> 08:33.394
And here's the bill for your car note.

08:33.702 --> 08:35.465
I hope they take it!

08:36.238 --> 08:38.467
Wait a minute, that's my car!

08:38.774 --> 08:40.241
Wait, come back!

08:41.543 --> 08:44.171
I hate that piece of shit!

08:45.213 --> 08:49.172
I'm tired of spending my time
waiting for you to quit acting like a child...

08:49.251 --> 08:52.550
and act like a grown man
for a change, Mays!

08:52.821 --> 08:54.789
I need to get on with my life!

08:54.856 --> 08:57.188
I want a house, l want children!

08:57.259 --> 09:00.387
I want to go on vacation!
You're horrible in bed!

09:00.996 --> 09:03.897
I am tired of being engaged.
I am tired of being--

09:08.136 --> 09:10.661
I wish you would.

09:15.110 --> 09:17.578
For the last time,
l'm not running for President.

09:17.646 --> 09:21.707
I'm not crazy! Gaines was 20 points behind.
It's ten weeks to Election Day.

09:21.783 --> 09:22.943
Damn it!

09:23.151 --> 09:26.780
They should have known better
than to talk on a cell phone in a plane.

09:26.855 --> 09:29.119
-What about Sanderson?
-That's a joke.

09:29.191 --> 09:31.455
Lewis has been Vice-President
for eight years.

09:31.526 --> 09:34.154
He's a war hero and Sharon Stone's cousin.
He can't lose.

09:34.229 --> 09:35.924
-What about Mosley?
-Girls.

09:36.031 --> 09:37.157
-Connelly?
-Boys.

09:37.232 --> 09:39.063
-McMasters?
-Big boys.

09:39.134 --> 09:41.500
So we concede the election to Lewis?

09:41.570 --> 09:45.631
Nobody is talking about conceding,
Debra, but let's get real here.

09:45.807 --> 09:47.399
We'll lose this one.

09:48.076 --> 09:51.637
The thing to do is to set the party up
for the next election.

09:51.813 --> 09:54.907
We need a candidate
that will put on a good show.

09:54.983 --> 09:58.384
This isn't a circus,
it's a presidential election.

09:58.954 --> 10:00.945
You can't just pick some guy...

10:01.623 --> 10:03.853
to run for President.

10:03.925 --> 10:07.190
It's unprecedented,
but if l put in a call to the party chairman...

10:07.262 --> 10:09.457
we find a candidate, he'll back him.

10:09.998 --> 10:12.330
Who will run a race
they know they can't win?

10:12.400 --> 10:13.867
Who says he has to know?

10:22.644 --> 10:23.804
What the....

10:35.257 --> 10:36.519
What now?

10:40.328 --> 10:41.920
No, not my bike!

10:47.836 --> 10:50.805
When l went in there
l wasn't thinking about being a hero.

10:50.872 --> 10:53.136
I wasjust trying to help Miss Pearl.

10:53.208 --> 10:54.539
Miss Pearl.

10:55.177 --> 10:56.906
I think we found our man.

10:57.445 --> 10:59.276
Look at this! This is great!

10:59.548 --> 11:01.539
This is America, see?

11:01.983 --> 11:05.146
Little guy against the big guy,
corporations against the people.

11:05.220 --> 11:07.120
Young versus old. What's better than this?

11:07.189 --> 11:08.986
Give me a break!

11:09.191 --> 11:11.716
I am going to run an alderman
for President?

11:12.894 --> 11:14.691
He's not an alderman.

11:14.963 --> 11:16.362
He's a hero.

11:17.365 --> 11:20.425
-Who doesn't like a hero?
-Big business loves a hero!

11:20.502 --> 11:21.662
See?

11:21.736 --> 11:24.136
You said we needed somebody
who can help the party.

11:24.206 --> 11:27.039
Now, how in the hell
does this guy help the party?

11:27.209 --> 11:28.676
I'm glad you asked.

11:29.311 --> 11:31.802
The United States is changing.
America is changing.

11:31.880 --> 11:33.973
Inside of 20 years, you know the numbers...

11:34.049 --> 11:37.951
20 percent black,
21 percent Asian, 39 percent Hispanic.

11:38.019 --> 11:42.183
The minorities will be the majority.
The smartest thing we can do...

11:42.357 --> 11:46.794
is be the first party
to nominate a minority for President.

11:46.995 --> 11:49.793
-How about a cripple?
-I don't think so, Charlie.

11:50.332 --> 11:54.462
Now, we'll lose, of course,
but the minorities will be happy.

11:54.936 --> 11:59.600
The minorities will be happy
and they will vote for us in 2008...

11:59.774 --> 12:01.605
because we've shown we support them.

12:01.676 --> 12:04.270
And the white people will vote for us...

12:04.646 --> 12:07.171
-because our guy isn't black.
-You got my vote!

12:07.249 --> 12:10.741
Geller, see if you can track down
this Mays Gilliam.

12:13.054 --> 12:14.919
Go check our accounts.

12:24.633 --> 12:27.966
Give me one good reason
why l should go along with this.

12:28.036 --> 12:31.870
Don't you get it, Debra?
l intend to run for President in 2008.

12:33.875 --> 12:37.003
Now give me one reason why you shouldn't.

12:41.149 --> 12:42.980
He would take a lot of work.

12:43.385 --> 12:45.353
We can run a background check...

12:45.420 --> 12:47.615
but it's obvious
he's not a party line candidate.

12:47.689 --> 12:50.385
He's just some kid
who thinks he can make a difference.

12:50.458 --> 12:53.325
Don't worry. Go out there,
put the machine behind him.

12:53.395 --> 12:56.330
You get 25 points in the polls,
consider it a win.

12:56.831 --> 12:58.924
Make sure he doesn't embarrass us.

12:59.000 --> 13:01.594
After this is over, we get to work.

13:02.971 --> 13:06.270
When l'm President, l'll take care of you.

13:08.643 --> 13:10.804
Help me. They locked me out of my office.

13:10.879 --> 13:13.609
I know. The mayor is fed up with you.

13:14.816 --> 13:18.047
How many times have l told you?
You got to quit trying to fix shit.

13:18.119 --> 13:21.247
I could've got you into the council
next term. Now you're red-lined.

13:21.323 --> 13:23.086
Shannon is taking over your district.

13:23.158 --> 13:26.616
They need to smooth over the mall
situation, that bus thing is heating up.

13:26.695 --> 13:29.721
-They don't trust you.
-I'm not the one stealing people's houses.

13:29.798 --> 13:32.892
That's what your problem is.
You got to work with us.

13:33.902 --> 13:36.530
That shit you pulled over there
cost the city money.

13:36.604 --> 13:38.595
Makes the mayor look bad.

13:38.940 --> 13:43.536
Now, contrary to popular belief,
politics is no place to express yourself.

13:43.745 --> 13:45.906
You want to get in, you got to fit in.

13:46.047 --> 13:48.982
And look at you.
Grow up, you got to dress better.

13:49.050 --> 13:51.678
Even Puff Daddy wears a suit to court.

13:54.389 --> 13:57.051
I'm sorry, brother, but ain't nothing l can do.

14:00.662 --> 14:02.823
-Nice car.
-Ain't it, though?

14:02.931 --> 14:05.456
Got it for a song at a repo auction.

14:28.223 --> 14:30.657
He feels bad, mighty low

14:30.725 --> 14:32.556
Got nowhere to go

14:32.961 --> 14:35.327
